            "body": "sigh. we have `is_disabled()` (why tf is this not named `is_enabled()`?), and these:\r\n\r\n```\r\ndisable({bufnr}, {namespace})                       *vim.diagnostic.disable()*\r\nenable({bufnr}, {namespace})                         *vim.diagnostic.enable()*\r\n```\r\n\r\nthose should be removed/deprecated and replaced with `enable + is_enabled`, just like `vim.lsp.inlay_hint`:\r\n\r\n```\r\nvim.lsp.inlay_hint.enable()\r\nvim.lsp.inlay_hint.is_enabled()\r\n```",
