            "body": "Hi @justinmk , Thank you for your response.\r\n\r\nMy issue is not to `disable()` and `enable()` the diagnostics. \r\nI would like to keep the diagnostics enabled and only change the way it is displayed (hidden / signcolumn / virtual text). Completely stopping and (re-)starting the diagnostics with `vim.cmd([[ LspRestart ]])` takes longer to process.\r\n\r\nIn my code-snippet the `vim.diagnostic.config({})` table is modified with a keyboard toggle. This works just fine, except the display is only updated **_after_** an `InsertLeave` event. To make the toggle instant I also trigger an `InsertLeave` event in the `refresh_diagnostics_screen()` function, but this seems like the wrong approach.\r\n\r\nAny guidance is highly appreciated.",
